===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Unger (1986)}} reconstructs Old Chinese pronunciation as *''pl(j)aŋʔ'' and considers this item part of a word family under {{och-l|陽}} and related to {{cog|th|ปลั่ง||bright}}.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} reconstructs OC *''br(j)aŋʔ'' and includes this in an {{der|zh|aav}} word family under {{och-l|亮}}. See there for more.

Finally, perhaps from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*brwaŋ||loud; bright}}; compare {{cog|my|ပြင်း||strong, violent}} (STEDT).

